---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '13 May 2026';
---
<BaseLayout title="Policies - EduRankAI" description="Hiring philosophy, data privacy, and terms of service.">

  <section class="px-[5vw] py-10 md:py-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto">

    <div class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-[0.62rem] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-burn font-bold mb-2">POLICIES</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,3rem)] font-semibold text-ink leading-[1.05] tracking-tight mb-3">
        How we work, <em class="italic text-burn font-medium">what we owe you.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[0.95rem] text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
        We try to be honest about our practices. If anything here is unclear or you have questions, please reach out via <a href="/contact" class="text-burn font-semibold hover:underline">Contact</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[0.75rem] text-ink-soft font-mono mt-2">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>

    <nav class="bg-cream-2 border border-ink/10 rounded-2xl p-4 mb-10">
      <p class="text-[0.62rem] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-ink-soft font-bold mb-2">On this page</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1 text-[0.85rem]">
        <a href="#hiring" class="text-burn hover:underline font-semibold">Hiring</a>
        <a href="#privacy" class="text-burn hover:underline font-semibold">Privacy</a>
        <a href="#terms" class="text-burn hover:underline font-semibold">Terms of Service</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <article id="hiring" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-[1.6rem] font-semibold text-ink leading-tight mb-3">Hiring Philosophy</h2>
      <div class="text-[0.95rem] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed space-y-4">

        <p><strong class="text-ink">What we look for.</strong> We hire for taste, judgment, and the ability to ship without supervision. Pedigree helps but does not substitute for proof of work. A strong portfolio link, a GitHub repo, a paper, a deployed product, a written critique - anything tangible - tells us more than a CV.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Our three principles.</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Proof over claims.</strong> Every candidate is asked to show real artifacts. We do not rely on resumes alone.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Honest stages.</strong> Applicants always know where they stand. Status is visible in the portal in real time. We do not ghost.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Senior evaluators.</strong> Candidates are interviewed by people at or above their target level. Junior engineers do not interview senior engineers.</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Compensation.</strong> Internships and apprenticeships at this stage are unpaid. Full-time roles are offered with real comp; details are discussed openly during the offer stage. We do not lowball - we share market context and our budget honestly. Equity (ESOP) is reserved for exceptional contribution.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Response time.</strong> We aim to respond within 5 business days of submission. If your application advances, you will hear quickly and clearly. If we do not move forward, we try to give honest, useful feedback rather than form rejections - though at scale this is not always possible.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">No tricks.</strong> We do not use timed take-home assignments meant to stress-test you. We do not require coding under surveillance. Our evaluation is centered on a live walkthrough of your past work, in-depth conversation, and (for senior roles) collaborative debugging or system design.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Reapplying.</strong> If we say no this time, you can reapply for a different role or after 6 months. Many of our best candidates came back stronger on a second application.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Bias and fairness.</strong> We do not use AI screening for application review. Every application is read by a human team member. We try to look beyond credentials to evaluate the actual person and their work.</p>

      </div>
    </article>

    <article id="privacy" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-[1.6rem] font-semibold text-ink leading-tight mb-3">Privacy</h2>
      <div class="text-[0.95rem] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed space-y-4">

        <p><strong class="text-ink">What we collect.</strong> When you apply for a role, we collect: your name, email, phone, city, LinkedIn (optional), resume/portfolio link, date of birth, optional birth time/place, photo (optional), education, work history, skills, proof-of-work artifacts you submit, and your written responses. We also log basic technical metadata: IP address, user agent, timestamp.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Why we collect it.</strong> Solely to evaluate your application and communicate with you about it. Birth time/place is optional and used only if you wish; we will never use it as a deciding factor.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Who can see it.</strong> Members of the EduRankAI hiring team. We do not share applicant data with third parties, advertisers, or external recruiters. We do not sell data.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">How long we keep it.</strong> Applicant data is retained for up to 24 months after a final decision (so we can revisit promising candidates and so you can reapply with context). After 24 months we delete or anonymize unless you have been hired or have an active candidacy.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Your rights.</strong> You can request a copy of your data, ask us to correct it, or ask us to delete it at any time by emailing <a href="mailto:hr@edurankai.in" class="text-burn font-semibold hover:underline">hr@edurankai.in</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Indian DPDP compliance.</strong> EduRankAI operates under the Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023 (India). Consent for processing your application is explicit (the consent checkbox on the final step of our Apply form). You may withdraw consent at any time, which will result in deletion of your application data.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Security.</strong> Applicant data is stored in encrypted Postgres (Neon Cloud, AWS Singapore region). Access is restricted to authenticated admin users on the EduRankAI team. Session cookies are httpOnly and secure. We do not use third-party analytics that fingerprint visitors.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Cookies.</strong> We use one essential session cookie for login functionality. We do not use advertising or tracking cookies.</p>

      </div>
    </article>

    <article id="terms" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-[1.6rem] font-semibold text-ink leading-tight mb-3">Terms of Service</h2>
      <div class="text-[0.95rem] text-ink-2 leading-relaxed space-y-4">

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Acceptance.</strong> By using edurankai.in or any associated product, you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the service.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Accurate information.</strong> When you apply for a role or create an account, you confirm that the information you provide is true and accurate. Misrepresentation may result in withdrawal of an offer or termination of employment.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Acceptable use.</strong> You agree not to: (a) submit false or fraudulent applications, (b) impersonate another person, (c) attempt to access accounts that are not yours, (d) probe or attempt to bypass the security of our systems, (e) scrape or harvest user data, (f) use the platform for any unlawful purpose.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Content you submit.</strong> Resumes, portfolios, written responses, and proof-of-work artifacts remain your intellectual property. By submitting, you grant EduRankAI a non-exclusive license to view, evaluate, and store your submission solely for hiring purposes.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Communication.</strong> Messages exchanged between you and the EduRankAI team via our in-app portal are stored in our database. Treat them as professional correspondence. Do not share confidential third-party information through our system.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Modifications.</strong> We may update these terms periodically. Material changes will be communicated via the portal or email. Continued use after changes means acceptance.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">No employment guarantee.</strong> Applying to a role does not constitute or guarantee an offer of employment. Any actual offer will be in writing and governed by a separate employment agreement.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Limitation of liability.</strong> EduRankAI provides this platform on an "as-is" basis. We are not liable for losses arising from your use of the platform beyond what is required by applicable Indian law.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Jurisdiction.</strong> These terms are governed by the laws of India. Disputes will be resolved in courts of competent jurisdiction in India.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Contact.</strong> For any questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:hr@edurankai.in" class="text-burn font-semibold hover:underline">hr@edurankai.in</a></p>

      </div>
    </article>

  </section>

</BaseLayout>
